# Superpowers workflow (org)

Use the **Superpowers** plugin skills for planning and building — not ad-hoc discovery.

| Situation | Skill (read before acting) |
|-----------|----------------------------|
| New feature, platform work, behavior change | `brainstorming` |
| Spec approved → implementation plan | `writing-plans` |
| Execute a written plan | `executing-plans` or `subagent-driven-development` |
| Bug or test failure | `systematic-debugging` |
| Feature or bugfix code | `test-driven-development` |
| Isolated feature work | `using-git-worktrees` |
| Before claiming done / commit / PR | `verification-before-completion` |
| Major step complete | `requesting-code-review` |

## Creative work gate

1. **No implementation** until design is presented and approved (unless user says skip SDLC).
2. Approved design → `docs/superpowers/specs/YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>-design.md`
3. Plans → `docs/superpowers/plans/YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>.md`

**Overrides:** obvious fixes; docs-only; user says "skip SDLC" / "no spec".

Project rules govern stack-specific test commands and doc paths.
